text: If you guys need any supplies, these prices are stupid cheap for some things
Lowest price I've seen on satin towers
In other news, David Leavitt confirms to the world he's a piece of human shit
Who's that?
Human spam bot that tries to be an mtg personality.
What a piece of shit.
He's faded out recently because so many people have blocked him. This is just his most recent display of assholery
I've seen him play on twitch
That's an ok joke
he was constantly running giveaways
Yea, I'm not one for outrage culture, but an hour after might be a little case of too soon
No, I defend his right to make that joke
Wish it were funnier
For sure.he definitely has the right to.
Doesn't make him an asshole if you ask me
Everything else he does, though...
That's fair
Not really - what's the intent behind making that joke that soon after a tragedy? I mean, what was his goal? Just getting yucks off folks current misery?
You can think he is a piece of shit, but I don't like the butthole clench reaction
Hope many hours should we wait?
But even on money draught, there are some things that are in too poor taste or a little too harsh in the moment still
He made a really lazy joke and I don't know what his goal was
I love shock and awe humor, but timing is all of it. That's my point of contention with this bad joke
But I agree with you completely, he has every right to make any bad joke he wants.
I'll concede to you on a lot of those points, <@U32LRG9NU>
I think it's unfair to call him a piece of shit
We aren't discussing his right to make the joke, but whether it makes him a shit for doing it while the bodies are warm.
Hack maybe
For this specifically
If he had waited until tomorrow, the joke would have felt forced and wouldn't have been worth making. That is maybe why he didn't wait. An experienced comic knows you don't make the joke, then
But he isn't an experienced comic. He's a dumb guy who tried too hard
I'd say an experienced coming doesn
need to make it fast becasue they don't need the shock
CK's snl child molesting joke last fall I think is just a good joke regardless of timing
The problem is I can't only defend comics I like.
Fair
Or joke-makers
First time I've heard of the guy myself, but I'm not in the loop
Oh, he's garbage
Most people blocked him
An hour is probably too soon. I don't know where the line is
But I made a joke about Chris Cornell this week. Am I a piece of shit?
My first thought is it's just kinda sad that you're that desperate for attention
Desperate is a accurate word for him
I'm desperate for attention for a living!
I mean, yea, calling his a piece of shit isn't accurate. Just a knee jerk reaction. Like Henry said, timing isn't the best.
Chis was a public figure so rules of propriety are different (you take the good, you take the bad, etc. ) but these are regular people who were either victims of a tragic accident or intent.
I still don't even know what happened in Manchester so I am not about to make a joke
Besides, some spoiled rock star hanging himself is silly and this isn't
I lived in Manchester for a few years and they had an IRA bombing in like 96 or 97 so they are really touchy

Which goes back to my original question about his intent in making the joke. If his humor was just to enhance his own self esteem, then he's a shit, vs. making a social commentary about a tragic event, etc.
I think that's the key, Cornell did that to himself. I don't think whoever was involved in whatever happened really volunteered for this kind of thing
So how do we feel about Jeselnek's joke about the Aurora CO theater shooting?
Sorry, I don't know that one.
or who that is
He said "Other than that, how was the movie?"
At least it's a good joke
I think shock humor is super hard to do well and I tend to stay away from it in my act because I see so many people who are new do it badly
Actually I think there's some social commentary to be found in that joke.
But I hate seeing comics get fired over funny tweets
I agree there - shock is crazy hard to do well, and it takes supreme commitment, since getting a likely bad reaction (and a whooping) comes with the territory.
Yea I never followed jeselnik so I'm in Henry's camp. I never heard the joke
That and I am friends with 1,200 open mic comics so I got to see the same "He's never gonna dance again" joke on Facebook 1,200 times

This is probably too meta but Jeselnek being an established comedian making a joke makes me think he's a guy who sees a chance to make a joke he thinks is funny. Coming from Random Guy 12 it feels like "look at meeeeee!!!!!!".
Well...that's really part of why comics are comics :wink:
Definitely. If you have no reputation to ruin, you aren't risking anything and are therefore sort of a troll
I guess just because you're not famous doesn't mean you don't think you've got a good joke to make
You guys are influencing my view in this more than you know
We're all brilliant
We're Jason's bullpen.
Time to workshop some material, boss.
We're something.
It's hard to know exactly why I react to some reactions. Your knee-jerk was to call him a piece of shit and my knee-jerk was to defend, which isn't easy or worth it
I can give you that elusive "45+ white guy" perspective all the kids are raving about.
The latest thing I am working on is that I hate gay dudes, but only because they are so good at everything and could bang my wife but don't and that's infuriating
Right? Isn't she good enough for them?

I think you hit the nail on the head <@U4V5EHQ2G> and <@U32LRG9NU>: he has nothing to lose except his already sterling reputation. It's really hard believing that he was trying to make a legit joke trying to be funny
Sure, but there's an art to navigate being hated and respected vs. just a dick.
I was actually proud of my Chris Cornell joke since it was subtle and so many jokes like it aren't
What was it?
A slow burn if you will?
"I've been to Detroit. I get it."
Now there's social commentary in that one. There is depth to plumb.
Ha, I did see that. I think I responded to to it
Yea I did
Now "I sure would have liked to see Chris Cornell when he was hanging around in Detroit" and 100 variants on that was my entire Facebook feed for a day
You aren't denigrating or minimizing the event, but drawing attention to the state of the city, etc.
Those suck balls.
Cleveland: at least we're not Detroit
Smelly, wrinkled and pickled balls.
Good talk
In summary, fuck David Leavitt
Ha, I'm glad even if our methods don't match, the math checks out
And since we're in off-topic, new Twin Peaks is aggressively Lynchian
Do I need some Showtime trial for that? That sounds like a pain
Have you heard the gospel of BitTorrent?
<@U32LRG9NU> I'm pretty sure Al Madrigal posted a link for a month free of Showtime recently. Not to bring him up, but if you're gonna binge...
My ISP is on my ass about my torrenting habits
For real? Sounds like you need a new ISP
Have you heard the gospel of the VPN?
Just spend thirty bucks on an amazon firestick and install kodi and a vpn on it
And watch all the things
I considered it
As an employee of Apple...I have not seen any part of this torrenting discussion.
I'm seeding your warez, Henry.
I don't want your seed, Dean
something something my wife says something something
Wow, Joyce carrol Oates talking shit about leavitt's joke on twitter
Or at least retweeting someone who did. No such thing as bad press I guess
